==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stenosis
<hw>Ste*no"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>steno`s</grk> narrow.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A narrowing of
the opening or hollow of any passage, tube, or orifice; <as>as,
<ex>stenosis</ex> of the pylorus</as>. It differs from
<xex>stricture</xex> in being applied especially to diffused rather than
localized contractions, and in always indicating an origin organic and
not spasmodic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stenostome</ent>⟦br⟧
